inline_comments.message:
If packages is null, prepareEnv will not run, and the CBA will not be uploaded to the executor.
Let's fix this edge case. If packages is null we can re-assign it to an empty list and always run prepareEnv

            if (packages == null) {
                // set env preparation log to empty...
                setAttribute(ATTRIBUTE_PREPARE_ENV_LOG, "".asJsonPrimitive())
                packages = mutableListOf<Object>().asJsonType()
            }
            prepareEnv(....)
